Magic for Beginners:
- 2 evocation (1 bolt, 1 ball), 5 utility (4 mage, +1 rogue), 1 heal (ranger only)
- detect monsters, detect traps/doors/stairs, detect object (rogue), light, phase door

Conjurings and Tricks:
- 2 debuff, 4 evocation (2 beam, 1 bolt, Wonder), 3 utility
- destroy t/d, cure pois, teleport

Incantations and Illusions:
- 3 evocation (2 bolts, Polymorph), 5 utility, 1 debuff
- satisfy hunger, recharge, dig, ID, detect vis/invis monsters

Sorcery and Evocations:
- 2 evocation (balls), 2 utility, 1 buff (haste), 1 debuff
- t/p other, detect object (ranger/mage)

Resistances:
- 5 buffs (elem resists, shield)

Raal's:
- 7 evocations (5 balls, 1 beam, 1 swarm)

Mordenkainen's:
- 5 utility
- create doors, stairs, t/p level, recall, glyph

Tenser's:
- 2 buffs (hero, berserk), 4 utility
- enchant armor, weapon, recharge 2, brand

Kelek's:
- 3 evocations (beam, bolt, ball), 1 debuff (conf-ball), 4 utility
- quake x2, banish x2

Primary utility spells (that all mage-types should get):
Detect monsters, traps/doors/stairs, invisible monsters
Light
Phase, teleport
Identify
Satisfy hunger
Recall

Existing buffs:
Offensive:
Haste
Berserk (+12 to-hit, -10 ac, res fear, -5% mag device)
Heroism (+24 to-hit, res fear, +5% mag device)
Defensive
Haste
Resist Fire/Cold/Pois
Resistance (4 basic + pois)
Shield (+50 AC)

Potential but nonexistent buffs:
Attack speed
Attack damage
Spell speed
Spell power

